721330f-a.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 43rd Street (East)
721330f-a.text:
Madison Avenue, west side, between 43rd and 44th Streets. The
headcuarters of Pease \& Elliman at 340 Madison Avenue will be
demolished in 192o and replaced by the National American Building,
about the same height.
The picture also shows detail of old St. Bartholomew's Church (1876),
which will be taken down in 1919 to make room for Canadian Pacific
Building. No. 338 on the left will be demolished at the same time.
1918.
C0ift of E.M. Jenks.
MAY BE REPnODUCED.
Ne. ~1638

721332f-a.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 43rd Street (East)
721332f-a.text:
Madison Avenue, east side, south from 44th to 43rd Street, showing
the newly built Canadian Pacific Building, No. 342.
The two small buildings, No. 336 and No. 340 (Pease 3 Ellman), will
be replaced in 1927 by modern buildings of the same size.
1921.
Ewing Galloway, Photographer.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
